# Documentation Guidelines

## Documentation Page Structure

Every component needs a documentation page at:
`src/app/docs/components/[component-name]/page.tsx`

## Page Template

```tsx
import { ComponentName } from '@/lib';

export const metadata = {
  title: 'ComponentName - Carbon Copy',
  description: 'Description of the component',
};

export default function ComponentNamePage() {
  return (
    <div className="docs-page">
      <h1>ComponentName</h1>
      <p className="lead">Brief description of what the component does.</p>

      {/* Basic Example */}
      <section>
        <h2>Basic Usage</h2>
        <div className="example">
          <ComponentName>Example content</ComponentName>
        </div>
        <CodeBlock language="tsx">{`
<ComponentName>Example content</ComponentName>
        `}</CodeBlock>
      </section>

      {/* Variants */}
      <section>
        <h2>Variants</h2>
        {/* Show each variant */}
      </section>

      {/* Props Table */}
      <section>
        <h2>Props</h2>
        <PropsTable props={[
          { name: 'variant', type: "'default' | 'dense'", default: "'default'", description: '...' },
          { name: 'className', type: 'string', default: '-', description: 'Additional CSS classes' },
        ]} />
      </section>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Required Sections

1. **Title & Description** - What the component is
2. **Basic Usage** - Simple example with code
3. **Variants** - All available variants with examples
4. **Props Table** - Complete prop documentation
5. **Accessibility** - Any a11y considerations
6. **Best Practices** - When and how to use

## Code Examples

- Show realistic, copy-pasteable examples
- Include imports in first example
- Keep examples focused and minimal
- Show common use cases

## Props Table Format

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| variant | 'default' \| 'dense' | 'default' | Visual style variant |
| className | string | - | Additional CSS classes |
| children | ReactNode | - | Content to display |

## Writing Style

- Use clear, concise language
- Focus on practical usage
- Include "do" and "don't" examples when helpful
- Reference related components
